<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« <a href="/news-04-2017">April 2017</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="/news-05-2017">May 2017</a></span> | <a href="/news-06-2017">June 2017</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<div style="margin: 10px; padding: 10px; border: 5px solid black; text-align: center; background-color: Moccasin;">
<h4 id="toc0"><span><span style="font-variant: small-caps;">News Time Capsule</span></span></h4>
<p>The dynamic nature of this wiki means that pages get moved, renamed, deleted, and replaced.<br />
Wiki links on old news pages have been made non-functional as many no longer point to the same content. External links and forum links are unaffected.</p>
</div>
<p>Welcome to this installment of site news, where we may have written up more than we can review!</p>
<p>This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</p>
<h4 id="toc1"><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The featured articles for this month are <a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-2354</a> (&quot;Reasonable Accommodations&quot;) by Niblic, <a class="newpage" href="#">His Name</a> by CirclesAndSquares, and <a class="newpage" href="#">'Rogue AI' (NVEO4/YVN3E/PN6UG)</a> by Doctor Cimmerian. The first is about the trouble caused by the Americans with Disabilities Act, the second is about amnestics gone horribly right, and the third is about a team of artificial intelligences infiltrating Marshall, Carter, and Dark. Check them out!</li>
<li>The featured articles for May were <a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-1172</a> (&quot;Double Word Scare&quot;) by deValmont, <a class="newpage" href="#">Document Alpha-Zeta-2</a> by Aeish, and our very first GOI-format featured article: <a class="newpage" href="#">GRANT REQUEST FOR THE CONSTRUCTION OF AN INTERSTELLAR SCIENCE VESSEL</a> by Greenwolf. The first is about a spooky game of Scrabble, the second's about&#8230;hm. What <em>was</em> it about? Anyways, the third is a Prometheus Labs-format about crafting black hole-powered spacecraft. Check them out!</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc2"><span>Event Featured Articles</span></h4>
<p>The theme for the month of May was <em>paradox</em>!</p>
<ul>
<li>In <a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-1505</a> (&quot;Paradoxical Avian Propagation&quot;), by LurkD, Hitchcock is one-upped by a raven in a time loop&#8230;</li>
<li>In <a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-2508</a> (&quot;The Long Wait&quot;), by Eekium, the <a class="newpage" href="#">Aleph Null</a> series kicks off with something abducting Foundation personnel&#8230;</li>
<li>And in <a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-711</a> (Paradoxical Insurance Policy), by Photosynthetic, the Foundation postpones Armageddon by stubbornly refusing to text itself&#8230;</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc3"><span>Rest of the News</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>It's the tenth anniversary of the one that started it all - that's right, <a class="newpage" href="#">SCP-173</a> turns ten this year! To celebrate, Dexanote is hosting the <a class="newpage" href="#">10 Years Birthday SCParty</a>! Check it out!</li>
<li>Kate McTiriss has returned from inactivity and has reclaimed her position on Operational Staff. Welcome back, Kate!</li>
</ul>
<p>Missing out on articles? Enjoy a recap on the articles from the past month. This month's blurbs were created by shaggydredlocks and Tretter. Great work, you two!</p>
